---
import LegalLayout from "@/layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import { CONTACT, SITE } from "@/data/site";
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How TradesBrain collects, uses, and protects your data."
  updated="Pending — set on publish"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how {SITE.name} (“we,” “us”) collects, uses,
    and protects information when you use the {SITE.name} mobile app and this
    website. We've built the structure below to cover what the app stores
    require; the binding legal wording is being completed with our counsel.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
  <p>The categories of information involved in providing TradesBrain include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Account information you provide (such as name, email, and trade).</li>
    <li>
      Job-related content you submit to Rex (such as questions, photos, and
      voice input) in order to receive answers.
    </li>
    <li>Subscription and billing details processed by our payment provider.</li>
    <li>Usage and device information collected to operate and improve the app.</li>
  </ul>
  <span class="placeholder">[ FOR LAWYER REVIEW ] — Confirm the exact data categories, retention periods, and lawful bases. Align with the app's actual data flows.</span>

  <h2>2. How we use your information</h2>
  <p>We use information to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide Rex's answers, reports, and quotes.</li>
    <li>Operate, secure, and improve the service.</li>
    <li>Process subscriptions and provide support.</li>
    <li>Communicate with you about the service.</li>
  </ul>
  <span class="placeholder">[ FOR LAWYER REVIEW ] — Confirm permitted uses and any secondary uses (analytics, model improvement). State clearly whether user content is used to train models.</span>

  <h2>3. Third-party providers</h2>
  <p>
    We rely on trusted third parties to deliver the service, including a payment
    processor (for subscriptions) and AI providers (to generate Rex's answers).
    These providers process data only as needed to perform their function.
  </p>
  <span class="placeholder">[ FOR LAWYER REVIEW ] — Name the specific processors (payment, AI, hosting, analytics), describe data shared with each, and link their terms / DPAs as required.</span>

  <h2>4. How we store and protect your data</h2>
  <span class="placeholder">[ FOR LAWYER REVIEW ] — Describe storage location, encryption, access controls, and retention/deletion practices.</span>

  <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, delete,
    or export your personal information, and to object to or restrict certain
    processing.
  </p>
  <span class="placeholder">[ FOR LAWYER REVIEW ] — Specify rights by jurisdiction (e.g. GDPR, CCPA/CPRA), how to exercise them, and response timelines.</span>

  <h2>6. Children's privacy</h2>
  <span class="placeholder">[ FOR LAWYER REVIEW ] — State minimum age and that the service is not directed to children.</span>

  <h2>7. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be
    reflected by the “Last updated” date above.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about your privacy? Email
    <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT.support}`}>{CONTACT.support}</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
